	   <tr><td colspan=2>Danko is 100% correct, and what stats do and don't do for tradeskills has been determined by parsing, AND by the developer in charge of tradeskills admitting as much at FanFaire.<br><br>WIS/INT (whichever is higher) will affect your trade skill up rate. OR, a secondary skill (STR for smithing, DEX for tailoring, etc) will take over if it is higher. The reason most tradeskillers go for wis/int is because its easier to have one set of stat gear rather than several different ones per tradeskill. However, most non-caster smiths that I know (including me) skilled up with +STR, since it is so ridiculously easy to get to 255 STR.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Sir Abazagaroth Katzkortulu<br>Knight of The Rathe<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=426463" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=426463</a></td></tr>
